				<section data-background-image="images/cover.jpg">
					<h2>WebP Server</h2>
					<p>A tool that will serve your JPG/PNGs as WebP format with compression, on-the-fly.</p>

				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>What's WebP</h2>
					<p>WebP is a modern image format that provides superior lossless and lossy compression for images on the web.
						 Using WebP, webmasters and web developers can create smaller, richer images that make the web faster.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Why WebP</h2>
					<p>
						WebP lossless images are 26% smaller in size compared to PNGs. WebP lossy images are 25-34% smaller than comparable JPEG images at equivalent SSIM quality index.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>Current Problems with WebP</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>Safari doesn't support it.</li>
						<li>Tons of Nginx and JavaScript works.</li>
						<li>It need a tool to transfer.</li>
						<li>mod_pagespeed is not easy to use.</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section data-background-image="images/webp.jpg">
